title._content: Photographic postcard of Henley Day on the Yarra Melbourne

description._content: Black-and-white postcard from Kookaburra series. Gold print at the top left reads: "Christmas Greetings" At the bottom left, white text reads: "HENLEY DAY ON THE YARRA, MELBOURNE". The postcard depicts the Yarra River with sculls racing in the centre, recreational boats and spectators line the river banks. Text on the reverse at the left side reads: 'Kookaburra' series Post Cards, 36 kinds, each with friendly/ motto3/-set". This card is listed as number 19. An image of a kookaburra is printed at the top left beside the animal reads: "LIFE IS A/ CAMERA/ LOOK PLEASENT/ PLEASE!” If reproduced or distributed, this image should be clearly attributed to the collection of the Australian National Maritime Museum; and not be used for any commercial or for-profit purposes without the permission of the museum. For more information see our Flickr Commons Rights Statement. The ANMM undertakes research and accepts public comments that enhance the information we hold about images in our collection. This record has been updated accordingly. Object number: 00045565
